headline: Machine Learning Engineer| Model Deployment & Optimization | Data Analysis & Visualization | AI/ML Research
text:
Machine Learning Engineer| Model Deployment & Optimization | Data Analysis & Visualization | AI/ML Research Hi, I’m Anu! I’m a Machine Learning Engineer passionate about designing scalable AI systems and deploying real-world ML solutions. With hands-on experience across healthcare and automotive domains, I thrive at the intersection of model optimization, cloud deployment, and impactful data analysis. 
My journey into Machine Learning began with a deep curiosity about how intelligent systems work and a desire to solve real-world problems using data. I enjoy diving into complex challenges and building models that can make a meaningful impact, whether it’s detecting disease patterns or automating systems to be smarter and more efficient. It’s this blend of creativity, logic, and purpose that draws me to this field. I see myself growing into a Machine Learning Engineer who not only codes but also contributes to innovations that help people and businesses thrive. 
Recently graduated from a Master’s in Engineering Data Analytics & Statistics at Washington University in St. Louis, I’ve led ML research projects that integrate automation, MLOps, and performance benchmarking. My recent work includes deploying a cloud-based kidney disease detection system using AWS SageMaker, Docker, and GitHub Actions—cutting deployment time by 70%. 
I also built NLP applications with Hugging Face, automated ML pipelines for summarization tasks, and optimized model performance using A/B testing. My technical stack spans Python, TensorFlow, PyTorch, LangChain, and cloud platforms like AWS and GCP.

🎯 What’s Next? 
I’m continuing to explore intelligent systems that solve real-world problems—from signal processing in healthcare to generative AI applications. My focus remains on optimizing ML workflows and developing robust, interpretable models ready for production.

name: Eduardo López-Pérez
headline: Data Scientist | Researcher in Artificial Intelligence | B.Sc. Mathematics & B.Sc. Physics
text:
Data Scientist | Researcher in Artificial Intelligence | B.Sc. Mathematics & B.Sc. Physics I am a Data Scientist and Researcher in Artificial Intelligence with 2+ year of experience. I have a background in Mathematics and Physics with a special focus in statistics. From that interest in statistics, I transitioned through data analysis and statistical modeling to machine learning and data science, where I found a field which really motivates me to learn more and more every day.

My current work involves using machine learning techniques to model industrial processes. I utilize a wide variety of algorithms such as SVMs, Gaussian Processes, Random Forests, Boosting methods or Deep Learning techniques, but my main focus is in Gaussian Processes due to their potential to be combined with Bayesian Optimization in order to optimize experimentation.

When working with industrial data, data quality can be a common issue, due to wrong measurements from sensors or other equipment, for this reason, working in outlier detection techniques and data filtering is also a significant amount of my work. Explainability in order to find the underlying physical relationships of each industrial process is something that I have done work on as well.

Apart from my current line of work, I have other scientific interests in fields such as finance, geopolitics, genomics and cybersecurity, and my goal is to strengthen my knowledge in each of those fields.

Long term plans: to continue learning new things about the fields I am interested in, and to work in high performance teams, facing new challenges.

Core values: integrity and respect, strong commitment, continuous improvement and innovation, focus on results.
